---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageDecor from '../components/PageDecor.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site.config';

const lastUpdated = 'May 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  path="/privacy"
  description="Privacy policy for Luma Pediatrics in McKinney, TX. How we collect, use, and protect information submitted through our website."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Privacy Policy', path: '/privacy' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="page-hero py-14 md:py-20 overflow-hidden">
    <PageDecor variant="minimal" sparkles={6} />
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center fade-up">
      <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-sm text-[var(--color-muted-foreground)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-20 md:pb-28 reveal">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose-luma">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Luma Pediatrics ("we," "us," "our") handles
        information submitted through our website at {SITE.domain}. Protected health information
        ("PHI") is handled separately under our <a href="/notice-of-privacy-practices">Notice of Privacy Practices</a>
        (HIPAA), which governs how we use and disclose health information in the course of care.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect information you voluntarily submit via our general inquiry form (name, email,
        message). Our contact form does not request your child's name, date of birth, or any
        medical detail — please call the office or use our patient portal for anything clinical.
      </p>
      <p>
        We also collect basic, non-personal log data automatically (IP address, browser type,
        referring URL, pages visited) to operate and improve the site.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to inquiries you send through the website.</li>
        <li>To verify insurance eligibility prior to a first visit, if you provide that information.</li>
        <li>To improve the website's performance, content, and accessibility.</li>
        <li>To comply with applicable law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we share information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your information. We share information only with service providers that help
        us operate the website and our practice (for example, our patient portal, email provider,
        hosting), and only as necessary to deliver those services. We may disclose information
        when required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies & analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Our website uses essential cookies for performance and may use privacy-respecting analytics
        to understand traffic. You can disable cookies in your browser; some features may not function as expected.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our website is directed to parents and guardians. We do not knowingly collect personal
        information from children under 13 through this website. Clinical care for minors is
        governed by HIPAA and our <a href="/notice-of-privacy-practices">Notice of Privacy Practices</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect information
        submitted through the website. No system is fully secure; please do not send sensitive
        clinical information through the contact form — use the secure patient portal instead.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the information you've submitted
        through the website by emailing <a href={SITE.contact.emailHref}>{SITE.contact.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date above will reflect changes.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email <a href={SITE.contact.emailHref}>{SITE.contact.email}</a>
        or write to {SITE.name}, {SITE.address.street}, {SITE.address.city}, {SITE.address.region} {SITE.address.postalCode}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-luma h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-foreground);
  }
  .prose-luma p,
  .prose-luma li {
    color: rgba(11, 29, 58, 0.85);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-luma ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-luma a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
